*:'''Finitude''': To be carefully distinguished from "mortality." '''Finitude''' refers not to the fact that man dies but to the fact that as a free choice of his own project of [[being]], he makes himself [[finite]] by excluding other possbilities each time he chooses the one which he prefers. Man would thus, because of his facticity, be [[finite]] even if [[immortal]].